<recipe>
	<name>Pickle:  Kinda Sorta Sours</name>
	<notes>If there were a picnic battle, fall in behind General Brown.  Alton serves up "Kinda Sorta Sours" which sound like something pulled from a cooler reverentially at certain BBQs.</notes>
	<ingredients>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1/2</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>onion</ingredient_name>
			<preparation>thinly sliced</preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>2</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>medium cucumbers</ingredient_name>
			<preparation>thinly sliced</preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>4</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>garlic cloves</ingredient_name>
			<preparation>smashed</preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1 cup</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>water</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1 cup</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>cider vineager</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1/2 cup</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>champagne vinegar (or other light vinnegar?)</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1/2 cup</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>sugar</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>2 Tbl + 2 tsp</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>kosher salt</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1 tsp</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>mustard seeds</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1/4 tsp</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>tumeric</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1 tsp</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>celery seeds</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1 tsp</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>pickling spice</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
	</ingredients>
	<preparation>In a clean spring-top jar combine onion, cucumbers and garlic cloves.

Boil water, cider and champagne vinegar, sugar, salt, mustard seeds, tumeric, celery seeds and pickling spice together in a non-reactive pot or pan.  Bring to a boil and simmer for four minutes.

Carefully pour pickling liquid over vegetable mixture, filling to top of jar.

Cool to room temperature before adding any additional liquid and refrigerate.

[Should note:  there should likely be some notes on the shelf life of such a product and its general care and handling during its lifetime]</preparation>
